1
00:00:10,905 --> 00:00:12,905
READY OR NOT: TEXAS

2
00:00:12,971 --> 00:00:15,505
CURRENT TIME:

3
00:00:17,871 --> 00:00:19,271
- Hey, Seo-jin.
- Yes?

4
00:00:19,338 --> 00:00:20,938
- I'm feeling it.
- Feeling what?

5
00:00:21,005 --> 00:00:22,071
See you in my dreams.

6
00:00:23,438 --> 00:00:25,705
DROWSINESS HITS YUNG-SUK
THE MOMENT THEY GET IN THE CAR

7
00:00:25,771 --> 00:00:28,271
- It hit me out of nowhere.
- Really?

8
00:00:28,338 --> 00:00:31,071
- I told you. I knew you'd get sleepy.
- I'll see you in the dreamland.

9
00:00:31,138 --> 00:00:32,538
Take your time.

10
00:00:32,605 --> 00:00:34,271
Enjoy your trip even if I don't join you.

11
00:00:34,338 --> 00:00:36,671
THAT MEANS "SLEEP TIGHT"

12
00:00:36,738 --> 00:00:37,605
See you soon.

13
00:00:37,671 --> 00:00:39,238
YUNG-SUK CLOSES HIS EYES

14
00:00:39,305 --> 00:00:41,705
Let's go to Fort Worth National Cemetery.

15
00:00:42,371 --> 00:00:45,505
A COWBOY RESTED HERE BRIEFLY

16
00:00:45,571 --> 00:00:49,171
It looks like we've gotten into the area
with ranch-style houses.

17
00:00:49,238 --> 00:00:51,171
INSTEAD OF THE NATIONAL CEMETERY,
THEY ARRIVED AT MODEST RANCH HOUSES

18
00:00:51,238 --> 00:00:52,338
I see a horse.

19
00:00:52,405 --> 00:00:54,571
MASCOT OF RANCH HOUSES: A HORSE APPEARS

20
00:00:54,638 --> 00:00:56,371
Hey, this guy's coat is in a lovely shade.

21
00:00:56,438 --> 00:00:58,205
My gosh. It's gleaming.

22
00:00:59,005 --> 00:00:59,905
Is that our stop?

23
00:00:59,971 --> 00:01:01,471
FINALLY REACHED THE COWBOYS' LODGINGS

24
00:01:02,638 --> 00:01:04,171
Is someone there?

25
00:01:04,238 --> 00:01:05,271
What?

26
00:01:05,771 --> 00:01:06,705
SIGHS

27
00:01:06,771 --> 00:01:08,338
Who's at my place?

28
00:01:09,271 --> 00:01:11,405
THE FIRST LODGING OF THE TRIP,
NOT HALF-ASLEEP YUNG-SUK'S HOUSE

29
00:01:13,971 --> 00:01:16,605
THE RUGGED WOODEN EXTERIOR
BLENDS PERFECTLY WITH NATURE

30
00:01:16,671 --> 00:01:19,671
IN THE KITCHEN GARDEN,
ENJOY A SELF-SUFFICIENT RANCH LIFE

31
00:01:19,738 --> 00:01:23,838
IN THE NEIGHBORING PASTURE,
ENJOY THE COWBOY LIFE

32
00:01:23,905 --> 00:01:26,805
"HOWDY"

33
00:01:26,871 --> 00:01:29,705
THEY'LL WRAP UP THEIR FIRST DAY
IN THIS FRIENDLY RANCH HOUSE

34
00:01:30,605 --> 00:01:32,238
I love this armchair.

35
00:01:32,305 --> 00:01:34,338
COMFY

36
00:01:34,405 --> 00:01:37,205
THE LEATHER ARMCHAIR ADDS THE TEXAN VIBE

37
00:01:37,271 --> 00:01:38,838
Try this black hat on, Seo-jin.

38
00:01:38,905 --> 00:01:41,905
THE BLACK COWBOY HAT YUNG-SUK BOUGHT

39
00:01:43,705 --> 00:01:45,238
APPRECIATIVE EXCLAMATION

40
00:01:46,671 --> 00:01:49,005
Your head must be smaller than mine.
It's rather tight.

41
00:01:49,071 --> 00:01:52,071
- No, your head is just relatively long.
- What?

42
00:01:52,138 --> 00:01:54,405
- My head is wider.
- It looks great on you.

43
00:01:54,471 --> 00:01:56,271
You look much younger wearing this.

44
00:01:58,038 --> 00:02:01,205
- Sorry, I didn't--
- I look like I'm dressed to impress now.

45
00:02:01,271 --> 00:02:03,138
I chose that to look like a working man.

46
00:02:03,205 --> 00:02:05,938
- But that looks better.
- Anyone would think you own a ranch.

47
00:02:06,005 --> 00:02:07,905
LIKE OWNING SEVERAL RANCHES

48
00:02:07,971 --> 00:02:11,638
Why does he look like a ranch owner,

49
00:02:11,705 --> 00:02:13,738
while we look like day laborers?

50
00:02:13,805 --> 00:02:16,771
Mr. Kim, good day.

51
00:02:16,838 --> 00:02:18,371
AN IMPROV TO EASE THE PAIN OF LABORERS

52
00:02:18,438 --> 00:02:20,171
Why are you suddenly so into improvs?

53
00:02:20,671 --> 00:02:25,205
I bet you two could rock those boots
in that outfit.

54
00:02:25,871 --> 00:02:27,438
- In this getup?
- Yes.

55
00:02:27,505 --> 00:02:29,505
Why don't we try them on?

56
00:02:29,571 --> 00:02:30,705
Yes, go ahead.

57
00:02:30,771 --> 00:02:31,938
RANCH OWNER CAJOLING LABORERS

58
00:02:32,005 --> 00:02:32,838
I'll go get…

59
00:02:32,905 --> 00:02:36,238
Seriously though,
Yung-suk is rocking that cowboy style.

60
00:02:36,971 --> 00:02:39,638
Can you play the violin
so we can dance to the music?

61
00:02:39,705 --> 00:02:42,238
- Let's get in there, Dae-ju.
- You could tour the wedding venues.

62
00:02:42,305 --> 00:02:44,838
Who looks better in them? Yung-suk, right?

63
00:02:44,905 --> 00:02:47,271
Are you ready, Dae-ju?
Let's start from the right foot.

64
00:02:47,338 --> 00:02:49,305
- Especially with the hat.
- Three, two, one.

65
00:02:52,705 --> 00:02:53,705
This is exciting.

66
00:02:53,771 --> 00:02:54,771
SQUEEZING HIS EYES SHUT

67
00:02:54,838 --> 00:02:55,905
ATTEMPTING A COSSACK DANCE

68
00:02:55,971 --> 00:02:57,271
Straighten your shoulders.

69
00:02:57,338 --> 00:02:58,638
We can do this.

70
00:02:58,705 --> 00:02:59,805
BETWEEN DISDAIN AND DELIGHT

71
00:02:59,871 --> 00:03:01,505
That's how you do it.

72
00:03:01,571 --> 00:03:04,271
Now that I'm used to them,
the boots aren't uncomfortable.

73
00:03:04,338 --> 00:03:05,505
They sure aren't.

74
00:03:05,571 --> 00:03:06,738
LAUGHING

75
00:03:06,805 --> 00:03:08,305
They're not uncomfortable.

76
00:03:08,871 --> 00:03:09,938
We find it uncomfortable.

77
00:03:10,005 --> 00:03:11,271
TOUCHÉ!

78
00:03:18,171 --> 00:03:19,971
How about a shooting contest tomorrow?

79
00:03:28,405 --> 00:03:31,271
He served in the Defense Security Command.

80
00:03:31,338 --> 00:03:32,805
Were you trained in shooting?

81
00:03:34,138 --> 00:03:36,805
I didn't shoot after the initial training
until reserve forces training.

82
00:03:36,871 --> 00:03:39,171
That's how it is most of the time.

83
00:03:39,238 --> 00:03:40,505
We've got a variety here.

84
00:03:40,571 --> 00:03:43,005
Seo-jin served in the Korean Army,
Yung-suk worked with the US Army…

85
00:03:43,071 --> 00:03:45,338
- I served in the Korean military too.
- Got it.

86
00:03:45,405 --> 00:03:47,905
Wait, he is the Korean Everyday Soldier.

87
00:03:47,971 --> 00:03:50,071
DAE-JU DID HIS MILITARY SERVICE
SOMEWHERE IN CHUNGCHEONG-DO

88
00:03:50,138 --> 00:03:54,238
The winner gets to order the others about,
and they'll have to go,

89
00:03:54,305 --> 00:03:56,205
"Understood, sir."

90
00:03:56,271 --> 00:03:57,705
COWBOY-STYLE OBEDIENCE

91
00:03:57,771 --> 00:03:58,971
Regardless of the order.

92
00:04:00,938 --> 00:04:03,171
You're dying to do that without the bet.

93
00:04:03,238 --> 00:04:05,238
I'm going to win.

94
00:04:05,305 --> 00:04:06,138
<i>I've got this.</i>

95
00:04:06,205 --> 00:04:07,905
FIRST DAY ENDS
WITH A DISCUSSION ON MILITARY SERVICE

96
00:04:07,971 --> 00:04:09,338
I think we can shoot now.

97
00:04:09,405 --> 00:04:10,605
CURRENT TIME:

98
00:04:10,671 --> 00:04:13,038
DAZED

99
00:04:13,105 --> 00:04:14,771
When did you wake up?

100
00:04:16,238 --> 00:04:17,471
- As if you have to ask.
- What?

101
00:04:17,538 --> 00:04:19,505
Hey, you're wearing the Netflix jacket.

102
00:04:19,571 --> 00:04:20,771
EMBARRASSED

103
00:04:20,838 --> 00:04:23,871
- You wore it right away.
- Seo-jin can be as meek as a lamb.

104
00:04:23,938 --> 00:04:25,338
BRIGHT RED TO KICK-START YOUR DAY

105
00:04:25,404 --> 00:04:28,305
- But he said he didn't want it.
- He never means it.

106
00:04:28,371 --> 00:04:29,971
SEO-JIN COMPLAINS MORE WHEN HE'S PLEASED

107
00:04:30,538 --> 00:04:33,438
It's bothersome to get dressed up
to go pick up our breakfast.

108
00:04:34,105 --> 00:04:37,471
To be honest, I woke up once at 3 a.m.

109
00:04:37,538 --> 00:04:39,638
I woke up at 1:40 a.m.

110
00:04:39,705 --> 00:04:42,705
I practically forced myself to sleep
with the hangover.

111
00:04:42,771 --> 00:04:44,171
So you got back to sleep?

112
00:04:44,238 --> 00:04:46,838
I got back up at 5 a.m.
and played a game for about an hour.

113
00:04:46,905 --> 00:04:48,171
No, I woke around 4:30 a.m.

114
00:04:48,238 --> 00:04:50,271
It's finally 6:30 a.m.
after a fitful sleep,

115
00:04:50,338 --> 00:04:53,438
tossing and turning,
passing time, and playing games.

116
00:04:53,505 --> 00:04:55,471
THEY STARTED THE DAY BRIGHT AND EARLY
DUE TO JET LAG

117
00:04:55,538 --> 00:04:57,238
AND DECIDED TO GET BREAKFAST FOR THE TEAM

118
00:04:57,305 --> 00:04:58,171
IT'S STILL VERY DARK

119
00:04:58,238 --> 00:04:59,971
Goodness, it's still dark outside.

120
00:05:00,038 --> 00:05:02,471
Seo-jin, it smells like summer.

121
00:05:03,171 --> 00:05:04,638
Because it is summer here.

122
00:05:04,705 --> 00:05:06,638
The scent is lovely.

123
00:05:06,705 --> 00:05:08,171
I'd like to sleep outdoors.

124
00:05:08,238 --> 00:05:10,205
- You could do that.
- Right?

125
00:05:10,271 --> 00:05:11,605
It's not cold at all, Seo-jin.

126
00:05:17,671 --> 00:05:20,671
It's currently 6:40 a.m.

127
00:05:21,738 --> 00:05:25,671
We learned from a survey
that Seo-jin woke up three hours ago.

128
00:05:25,738 --> 00:05:28,171
Why is it so dark still?

129
00:05:28,238 --> 00:05:31,405
ON THE LEFT, YUNG-SUK
ON THE RIGHT, SEO-JIN

130
00:05:31,471 --> 00:05:33,905
- We're going in the right way, right?
- Yes.

131
00:05:33,971 --> 00:05:35,905
OFF WE GO TO GET BREAKFAST

132
00:05:35,971 --> 00:05:39,638
What's a pro tip for when you get
pulled over by the police in the US?

133
00:05:41,438 --> 00:05:42,771
- Apologize.
- What?

134
00:05:42,838 --> 00:05:44,171
Say you're sorry.

135
00:05:45,538 --> 00:05:48,338
I mean, you must have something else.

136
00:05:48,405 --> 00:05:50,338
You pull over right away.

137
00:05:50,405 --> 00:05:51,671
- Right away?
- Yes.

138
00:05:52,205 --> 00:05:54,205
Just pull over
if police stop you in the US.

139
00:05:54,771 --> 00:05:56,471
Wait to open your window until instructed.

140
00:05:56,538 --> 00:05:59,038
Keep your hands on the wheel and stay put.

141
00:06:00,871 --> 00:06:04,238
I'm surprised we're still not in Dallas.

142
00:06:05,971 --> 00:06:08,638
We haven't reached Dallas yet, have we?

143
00:06:09,338 --> 00:06:10,905
We're circling the neighboring areas.

144
00:06:10,971 --> 00:06:15,071
It's like landing in Incheon Airport
and roaming around Cheongna.

145
00:06:15,738 --> 00:06:17,571
- We're here.
- Is this the place?

146
00:06:17,638 --> 00:06:19,305
Where's Ell's Place?

147
00:06:19,371 --> 00:06:20,938
Is it the red building there?

148
00:06:21,005 --> 00:06:22,771
Over there. It says Ell's Place.

149
00:06:23,438 --> 00:06:25,038
It looks nice.

150
00:06:25,105 --> 00:06:28,705
THE RED EXTERIOR
MATCHES SEO-JIN'S RED JACKET

151
00:06:34,605 --> 00:06:37,838
WHEN YOU OPEN THE WOODEN DOOR…

152
00:06:38,371 --> 00:06:40,238
Doesn't it look like a set?

153
00:06:47,071 --> 00:06:47,905
Let's sit and wait.

154
00:06:47,971 --> 00:06:49,271
THE JET-LAGGED TEAM GOT HERE TOO EARLY

155
00:06:54,038 --> 00:06:57,005
STARTS STUDYING THE MENU

156
00:06:57,071 --> 00:07:00,071
Oh, they have burritos.

157
00:07:00,138 --> 00:07:03,205
- We're getting them tomorrow.
- That's true. So for today…

158
00:07:04,138 --> 00:07:05,605
What are you getting?

159
00:07:05,671 --> 00:07:06,671
This one.

160
00:07:14,471 --> 00:07:16,305
- Should we get five?
- Yes, five.

161
00:07:24,138 --> 00:07:26,438
Why don't we order a French toast?

162
00:07:26,505 --> 00:07:27,471
It looks so good.

163
00:07:27,538 --> 00:07:29,071
Should I call for the waitress?

164
00:07:29,138 --> 00:07:31,405
Let's order the French toast, full.

165
00:07:31,905 --> 00:07:33,771
- Let's get the half option.
- No, the full one.

166
00:07:33,838 --> 00:07:35,738
We could easily finish it.

167
00:07:36,238 --> 00:07:38,971
- Why the sudden greed over food?
- It's just…

168
00:07:39,038 --> 00:07:41,405
- I feel like having a French toast--
- Have it tomorrow.

169
00:07:41,471 --> 00:07:42,805
Come on, place an order for me.

170
00:07:42,871 --> 00:07:44,071
- The French toast.
- You really…

171
00:07:54,071 --> 00:07:57,038
Wow, she has that Southern accent.

172
00:07:57,105 --> 00:07:59,705
Right? The one you hear in movies.

173
00:07:59,771 --> 00:08:02,771
It makes you sound like
you're munching something.

174
00:08:02,838 --> 00:08:05,738
THE SLOW-PACED TEXAN TWANG
HAS A SONOROUS CHARM

175
00:08:22,305 --> 00:08:24,971
DON'T MISS FREE PUBLICITY

176
00:08:27,005 --> 00:08:29,071
FOOD PACKED IN NO TIME

177
00:08:30,538 --> 00:08:35,071
HEADING BACK TO THE LODGING
WITH HANDS FULL

178
00:08:35,638 --> 00:08:37,471
We only bought five platters.

179
00:08:37,538 --> 00:08:38,671
Wait, did we get four?

180
00:08:38,738 --> 00:08:40,905
- These are the platters.
- That's right.

181
00:08:40,971 --> 00:08:42,371
Oh, there's soup.

182
00:08:43,605 --> 00:08:44,971
The salad looks pretty good.

183
00:08:45,038 --> 00:08:46,471
SALAD WITH LOTS OF BACON

184
00:08:46,538 --> 00:08:48,005
It's the perfect breakfast.

185
00:08:48,071 --> 00:08:49,571
IT'D BE A SHAME NOT TO HAVE PANCAKES!

186
00:08:50,905 --> 00:08:53,305
TRYING OUT THE SOUP FIRST

187
00:08:53,905 --> 00:08:55,405
Is this cream soup?

188
00:08:56,038 --> 00:08:58,371
- Seems like it goes with the biscuits.
- It's good.

189
00:08:59,038 --> 00:09:01,171
Doesn't it taste like the soup

190
00:09:01,238 --> 00:09:03,338
served as an appetizer
in Korean-Western restaurants?

191
00:09:03,405 --> 00:09:05,171
That's exactly it.

192
00:09:05,238 --> 00:09:08,005
- The one with a strong peppery taste.
- Yes.

193
00:09:09,971 --> 00:09:13,271
It may look simple,
but it tastes as good as KFC's food.

194
00:09:13,338 --> 00:09:15,238
I read an article just a few days ago.

195
00:09:15,305 --> 00:09:17,505
KFC recently moved
their headquarters to Texas,

196
00:09:18,205 --> 00:09:20,271
and the State of Kentucky
voiced their deep disapproval.

197
00:09:20,338 --> 00:09:21,938
It's named KFC, after all.

198
00:09:23,105 --> 00:09:26,905
See? Everyone's relocating to Texas.

199
00:09:28,138 --> 00:09:29,205
Everyone's coming here.

200
00:09:29,271 --> 00:09:31,571
ACCORDING TO SEO-JIN,
TEXAS IS THE HOTTEST STATE IN THE US

201
00:09:32,371 --> 00:09:34,171
LICKING

202
00:09:34,238 --> 00:09:36,871
What's with the finger licking?

203
00:09:36,938 --> 00:09:38,738
I ate the food with my hands.

204
00:09:42,005 --> 00:09:42,971
You can have this.

205
00:09:43,038 --> 00:09:44,838
Wait, it's Seo-jin's. One's for Seo-jin…

206
00:09:44,905 --> 00:09:47,605
Hey, don't touch things
after licking your fingers.

207
00:09:47,671 --> 00:09:49,671
- Take this.
- You're unbelievable.

208
00:09:53,705 --> 00:09:56,905
KFC's packaging
has "finger-licking good" on it.

209
00:09:56,971 --> 00:09:58,705
IT'S FINGER LICKIN' GOOD
KFC'S FAMOUS SLOGAN

210
00:09:58,771 --> 00:10:00,538
Lick your finger at a KFC, then.

211
00:10:00,605 --> 00:10:02,005
Don't do it here.

212
00:10:03,171 --> 00:10:05,005
Gosh, you sound so sweet.

213
00:10:05,905 --> 00:10:08,171
Don't you just love the tone he's using?

214
00:10:08,238 --> 00:10:10,171
- Go wash your hands.
- The weather's lovely.

215
00:10:10,238 --> 00:10:11,738
HE'S PUTTING HIS HANDS IN HIS POCKETS

216
00:10:11,805 --> 00:10:14,171
Go wash your hands, will you?

217
00:10:14,238 --> 00:10:15,338
WORRISOME SENSE OF HYGIENE

218
00:10:15,405 --> 00:10:18,005
- He put them in his pockets.
- Why do I need to wash my hands?

219
00:10:18,071 --> 00:10:19,671
I only need to wash them before bedtime.

220
00:10:19,738 --> 00:10:21,638
Why should I do it more and waste water?

221
00:10:21,705 --> 00:10:24,038
Did you just put your hands there
after licking your fingers?

222
00:10:24,105 --> 00:10:25,471
I'll need to lick them again.

223
00:10:27,938 --> 00:10:29,071
Oh, jeez.

224
00:10:29,138 --> 00:10:31,638
THIS IS WHEN YOU CAN COMPLAIN
THAT YUNG-SUK IS RUINING YOUR APPETITE

225
00:10:31,705 --> 00:10:35,171
THE PEACEFUL BREAKFAST TIME ENDS

226
00:10:39,238 --> 00:10:42,105
FIT CHECK COMPLETE

227
00:10:45,338 --> 00:10:46,305
Should I put this on?

228
00:10:48,105 --> 00:10:53,005
CAREFUL

229
00:10:54,271 --> 00:10:57,371
You're actually rocking it.
It looks pretty good with that hat.

230
00:10:57,438 --> 00:10:58,471
SIGHS

231
00:10:58,538 --> 00:11:00,738
A SUDDEN TRANSITION
INTO HIS COWBOY PERSONA

232
00:11:00,805 --> 00:11:01,738
Why does it suit you?

233
00:11:03,205 --> 00:11:04,805
YUNG-SUK HAS LONG ADMIRED COWBOYS

234
00:11:04,871 --> 00:11:06,971
HE'S EAGERLY WAITED
FOR HIS STAY IN THE RANCH HOUSE

235
00:11:10,705 --> 00:11:12,105
Tell me, Ye-seul.

236
00:11:13,071 --> 00:11:16,005
How's the sales plan for our ranch going?

237
00:11:16,071 --> 00:11:16,905
I hear…

238
00:11:16,971 --> 00:11:17,805
A RANDOM IMPROV BEGINS

239
00:11:20,305 --> 00:11:23,438
…Mr. Brown's pregnant buffalo

240
00:11:23,505 --> 00:11:26,238
delivered three calves this morning.

241
00:11:27,071 --> 00:11:30,505
Ye-seul, how many buffalo
do we have at our ranch?

242
00:11:30,571 --> 00:11:33,371
PLEASE STOP

243
00:11:33,438 --> 00:11:36,505
SEO-JIN IS GETTING READY
WHILE YUNG-SUK ENJOYS HIS IMPROV ACT

244
00:11:36,571 --> 00:11:38,571
IT'S TAKING HIM AGES TO PUT THEM ON

245
00:11:38,638 --> 00:11:41,471
People may misunderstand you
if you wear them to restaurants.

246
00:11:42,205 --> 00:11:44,538
They might think you're dawdling
to avoid paying.

247
00:11:44,605 --> 00:11:47,505
People might get the wrong idea, Seo-jin.

248
00:11:47,571 --> 00:11:48,738
Should we go?

249
00:11:49,471 --> 00:11:51,605
It's a beautiful day for shooting.

250
00:11:51,671 --> 00:11:53,971
OFF THEY GO TO THE SHOOTING RANGE!

251
00:11:54,038 --> 00:11:56,971
Here's my impression of Texas.

252
00:11:57,038 --> 00:11:58,571
A farmer made rich by oil wells.

253
00:11:59,305 --> 00:12:01,271
Wouldn't you agree?

254
00:12:01,338 --> 00:12:02,605
TEXAS HAS LONG BEEN SEEN
AS A FARMING STATE

255
00:12:02,671 --> 00:12:04,305
BUT ITS BIGGEST INDUSTRY NOW
IS ENERGY PRODUCTION

256
00:12:04,371 --> 00:12:06,471
Texans take a massive pride in that.

257
00:12:06,538 --> 00:12:11,371
- Do they really?
- They don't take federal support.

258
00:12:11,871 --> 00:12:14,138
Do they receive no federal funding?

259
00:12:14,205 --> 00:12:15,638
TEXAS DOES RECEIVE FEDERAL FUNDING

260
00:12:15,705 --> 00:12:18,405
BUT THE STATE'S TAXES-FEDERAL FUNDING RATE
IS LOW DUE TO ITS HUGE ECONOMY

261
00:12:18,471 --> 00:12:21,205
Look. The US flag and the Texas flag.

262
00:12:21,905 --> 00:12:23,338
They're flying side by side.

263
00:12:23,405 --> 00:12:25,138
TWO FLAGS ARE FLYING AT THE SAME LEVEL

264
00:12:25,205 --> 00:12:29,138
Did Bush Sr. and Bush Jr.

265
00:12:29,205 --> 00:12:31,405
both serve as the governor of Texas?

266
00:12:31,471 --> 00:12:33,605
Not Bush Sr., no.

267
00:12:33,671 --> 00:12:37,138
- But Bush Jr.--
- He did serve as the governor.

268
00:12:37,205 --> 00:12:40,038
Bush Sr. was a career politician,

269
00:12:40,105 --> 00:12:44,171
whereas Bush Jr. was a businessman
who raked in money from a Texan business.

270
00:12:44,238 --> 00:12:45,438
So he was a businessman?

271
00:12:45,505 --> 00:12:47,005
That investment changed his life.

272
00:12:47,071 --> 00:12:49,138
So with that huge jackpot,

273
00:12:49,838 --> 00:12:52,071
he ran for the gubernatorial election.

274
00:12:52,138 --> 00:12:54,671
He won, and that paved his way
to the presidential election.

275
00:12:54,738 --> 00:12:59,705
Still, didn't the Bush family
have a family business or something?

276
00:13:00,605 --> 00:13:02,638
"Bush family."

277
00:13:02,705 --> 00:13:04,038
SEARCHING THE WEB

278
00:13:04,671 --> 00:13:07,005
Can you guess
what their family business is?

279
00:13:07,071 --> 00:13:08,438
It says "running for presidency."

280
00:13:09,105 --> 00:13:10,771
Apparently, that's their family business.

281
00:13:10,838 --> 00:13:12,271
THAT'S AN AWE-INSPIRING FAMILY BUSINESS

282
00:13:12,338 --> 00:13:16,305
Tell us about this, then.
We're on our way to the shooting range.

283
00:13:16,371 --> 00:13:19,005
If the US adopts gun control like Korea,

284
00:13:20,005 --> 00:13:22,638
wouldn't the crime rates drop?

285
00:13:22,705 --> 00:13:25,105
I'm not an expert in policy matters.

286
00:13:25,738 --> 00:13:28,138
But rather than introducing a ban

287
00:13:28,971 --> 00:13:32,305
that could potentially lead
to black market operations,

288
00:13:32,371 --> 00:13:35,938
they want the authorities
to be in charge of the legalized market.

289
00:13:36,005 --> 00:13:38,138
At least, that's how I understand it.

290
00:13:38,205 --> 00:13:41,071
If there were a total ban,
the black market would flourish.

291
00:13:41,138 --> 00:13:42,738
- Just like drugs?
- Exactly.

292
00:13:42,805 --> 00:13:45,538
You need an identification
to get a license.

293
00:13:45,605 --> 00:13:48,271
They seemed to have this strong belief

294
00:13:48,338 --> 00:13:51,871
that each individual is responsible
for keeping their family and home safe.

295
00:13:51,938 --> 00:13:54,571
Many Americans enjoy hunting as a hobby.

296
00:13:54,638 --> 00:13:56,671
I wonder how many keep a gun here.

297
00:13:56,738 --> 00:13:58,105
About half of the population?

298
00:13:58,171 --> 00:13:59,405
- What?
- The ratio?

299
00:13:59,471 --> 00:14:01,005
Yes, out of all households…

300
00:14:01,838 --> 00:14:05,405
It's 36%.
That's about the median of the US.

301
00:14:05,471 --> 00:14:07,571
- 36%?
- Yes, it's for Texas.

302
00:14:07,638 --> 00:14:10,271
The protagonist of <i>American Sniper</i>
is from Texas.

303
00:14:10,338 --> 00:14:13,671
You sure love movies.
You've watched <i>American Sniper</i> too?

304
00:14:14,438 --> 00:14:16,371
What? It was a huge hit.

305
00:14:17,671 --> 00:14:19,705
But out here in Texas,

306
00:14:19,771 --> 00:14:21,771
people don't use a rifle like the M16.

307
00:14:21,838 --> 00:14:23,205
- I wouldn't know.
- You know,

308
00:14:23,271 --> 00:14:25,838
cowboys in Western movies use shotguns.

309
00:14:26,505 --> 00:14:29,005
Guys in the military would use an M16.

310
00:14:29,071 --> 00:14:31,305
Are we making the wrong choice here?

311
00:14:31,371 --> 00:14:34,671
We're supposed to try shotguns
to blow a hole or something.

312
00:14:34,738 --> 00:14:36,171
- I'm not sure.
- What?

313
00:14:36,238 --> 00:14:38,505
I'm not so sure
if we're dressed for the occasion.

314
00:14:39,605 --> 00:14:41,205
Should we have worn uniforms?

315
00:14:41,271 --> 00:14:43,571
We should try out shotguns, not others.

316
00:14:43,638 --> 00:14:46,805
We have Mr. Defense Security Command,
Mr. KATUSA,

317
00:14:46,871 --> 00:14:48,771
and Mr. Everyday Soldier competing today.

318
00:14:48,838 --> 00:14:50,905
SOON TO FIND OUT THE BEST KOREAN SNIPER

319
00:14:51,471 --> 00:14:53,638
How about the losers pay for lunch?

320
00:14:54,205 --> 00:14:55,371
What do you think?

321
00:14:55,938 --> 00:14:56,938
I'm in.

322
00:14:57,471 --> 00:15:00,438
You seem very confident
for someone who's rarely handled a gun.

323
00:15:01,705 --> 00:15:03,871
I was the best shooter in the camp.

324
00:15:03,938 --> 00:15:05,605
- Really?
- I nailed all my marks.

325
00:15:05,671 --> 00:15:06,938
All 20 shots.

326
00:15:07,005 --> 00:15:09,271
But you had a good vision then.

327
00:15:09,338 --> 00:15:11,205
You wouldn't have had farsightedness.

328
00:15:11,271 --> 00:15:13,538
- "Defender Outdoors"?
- "Defender Outdoors"?

329
00:15:15,538 --> 00:15:17,405
This is my shot
at winning Seo-jin's 100 bucks.

330
00:15:18,138 --> 00:15:20,771
I'm getting just a bit anxious.

331
00:15:20,838 --> 00:15:22,805
- Why?
- Just because.

332
00:15:22,871 --> 00:15:24,471
- Because we'll be shooting?
- Yes.

333
00:15:25,238 --> 00:15:27,638
Come on. It's not as if you're the target.

334
00:15:28,138 --> 00:15:29,671
WALKING IN FEELING NERVOUS AND EXCITED

335
00:15:29,738 --> 00:15:30,938
Look at those guns.

336
00:15:31,005 --> 00:15:33,471
A WIDE RANGE OF GUNS WELCOMES THEM

337
00:15:33,538 --> 00:15:35,438
RIGHT UPON ENTRY

338
00:15:36,038 --> 00:15:39,038
IT OFFERS A VARIETY OF GUN-RELATED GOODS

339
00:15:39,105 --> 00:15:42,338
AS WELL AS AN INDOOR PRACTICING RANGE

340
00:15:42,405 --> 00:15:44,505
We can touch them, right?

341
00:15:44,571 --> 00:15:46,271
- Are we allowed to touch them?
- I suppose.

342
00:15:46,338 --> 00:15:47,305
EVERYONE GRABS A FIREARM

343
00:15:47,371 --> 00:15:48,705
- My gosh.
- This is pretty heavy.

344
00:15:48,771 --> 00:15:51,305
I've never held a pistol before.

345
00:15:51,371 --> 00:15:53,305
It's rather scary, guys.

346
00:15:53,838 --> 00:15:55,838
SCARED

347
00:15:56,505 --> 00:15:59,238
- This is a first for me. What about you?
- The weight sure feels different.

348
00:15:59,305 --> 00:16:00,771
Pistol? I've never held one…

349
00:16:00,838 --> 00:16:03,338
No, I've actually held one.
Not a Beretta, though.

350
00:16:03,405 --> 00:16:04,671
Hey, look.

351
00:16:04,738 --> 00:16:07,138
You can see the target zone.

352
00:16:07,938 --> 00:16:09,005
You look pretty cool.

353
00:16:09,071 --> 00:16:10,271
THE AIMING POINT VISIBLE ABOVE THE HANDGUN

354
00:16:10,338 --> 00:16:12,205
- Where are you aiming, though?
- What?

355
00:16:12,271 --> 00:16:14,238
CLICK-CLACK

356
00:16:15,805 --> 00:16:16,638
Hey, this is…

357
00:16:16,705 --> 00:16:18,005
WORRIED

358
00:16:18,071 --> 00:16:20,205
MOVE TO THE RANGE TO SHOOT AT THE TARGETS

359
00:16:23,471 --> 00:16:25,171
We were never trained this way back home.

360
00:16:25,238 --> 00:16:28,371
We either took a shot
lying down or crouching down.

361
00:16:28,438 --> 00:16:30,605
Only officers shot this way.

362
00:16:30,671 --> 00:16:32,405
I've never seen anyone shoot standing.

363
00:16:32,471 --> 00:16:33,305
It's just…

364
00:16:49,871 --> 00:16:51,071
IT'S A PLEASURE

365
00:16:59,671 --> 00:17:01,638
WHEN YOU SHOOT A HANDGUN,
ITS SLIDE MOVES BACK

366
00:17:01,705 --> 00:17:03,438
KEEP YOUR FINGER TO THE SIDE
FOR YOUR SAFETY

367
00:17:23,805 --> 00:17:24,638
SEO-JIN'S PICK:

368
00:17:24,705 --> 00:17:27,305
SUITABLE EVEN FOR BEGINNERS
OFTEN USED FOR SELF-DEFENSE PURPOSES

369
00:17:30,738 --> 00:17:32,471
FILMED SAFELY UNDER EXPERT SUPERVISION

370
00:17:33,038 --> 00:17:34,771
SEO-JIN'S TARGET

371
00:17:34,838 --> 00:17:37,171
SEO-JIN PULLED
THE FIRST TRIGGER OF THE DAY

372
00:17:37,771 --> 00:17:39,671
BULL'S-EYE!

373
00:17:39,738 --> 00:17:42,038
THE SHOTS AFTER…

374
00:17:45,638 --> 00:17:46,605
ALL PIERCED THE CENTER

375
00:17:46,671 --> 00:17:47,838
It's over.

376
00:17:50,638 --> 00:17:52,405
A SATISFACTORY FIRST EXPERIENCE
WITH THE HANDGUN

377
00:17:52,471 --> 00:17:55,171
NEXT UP IS DAE-JU, MR. FULL-TIME RESERVE

378
00:17:55,238 --> 00:17:56,071
DAE-JU'S PICK:

379
00:17:56,138 --> 00:17:58,305
OFTEN USED IN COMPETITIONS,
MINIMAL ALLOWS QUICK AND PRECISE SHOTS

380
00:17:58,371 --> 00:17:59,571
Oh my. This is scary.

381
00:17:59,638 --> 00:18:01,171
Be careful, Dae-ju.

382
00:18:03,071 --> 00:18:04,838
DAE-JU'S FIRST SHOT MISSES THE TARGET

383
00:18:04,905 --> 00:18:05,971
BUT THE FOLLOWING SHOTS…

384
00:18:07,405 --> 00:18:09,171
BULL'S-EYE #1

385
00:18:09,238 --> 00:18:10,371
BULL'S-EYE #2

386
00:18:10,438 --> 00:18:11,771
DAE-JU IS GETTING THE HANG OF IT

387
00:18:11,838 --> 00:18:15,405
Our Mr. Full-time Reserve
is killing it right now.

388
00:18:15,471 --> 00:18:16,971
PLEASED

389
00:18:17,038 --> 00:18:18,371
He's a good shot.

390
00:18:18,438 --> 00:18:21,171
I didn't expect the recoil at first.

391
00:18:21,238 --> 00:18:23,338
Mr. Defense Security Command
is dead last for now.

392
00:18:23,405 --> 00:18:25,038
Kudos, Mr. Full-time Reserve.

393
00:18:25,105 --> 00:18:26,105
HURT

394
00:18:28,171 --> 00:18:29,938
HOW GOOD A SHOT IS THE TEASING MR. KATUSA?

395
00:18:30,005 --> 00:18:31,671
YUNG-SUK'S PICK:

396
00:18:31,738 --> 00:18:33,405
SUPERLATIVE PRECISION AND SPEED

397
00:18:33,471 --> 00:18:35,171
YUNG-SUK'S TARGET

398
00:18:36,305 --> 00:18:37,838
A BULL'S-EYE FROM THE GET-GO!

399
00:18:37,905 --> 00:18:38,771
My gosh.

400
00:18:38,838 --> 00:18:40,171
SURPRISED

401
00:18:40,238 --> 00:18:42,938
YUNG-SUK KEEPS HITTING DEAD CENTER

402
00:18:43,005 --> 00:18:44,605
Hey, he's good.

403
00:18:44,671 --> 00:18:46,038
HIS DIMPLES DEEPEN AT THE SURPRISE

404
00:18:48,071 --> 00:18:50,271
EVEN HIS FINAL SHOT GETS A 10

405
00:18:50,338 --> 00:18:51,338
YOU HAVE MY RESPECT

406
00:18:52,938 --> 00:18:54,838
DID YOU ALL SEE THAT?

407
00:18:54,905 --> 00:18:57,805
MR. KATUSA CAN PULL HIS WEIGHT

408
00:18:57,871 --> 00:18:58,738
Good job.

409
00:18:59,571 --> 00:19:01,638
You both suck.

410
00:19:01,705 --> 00:19:02,671
I'm the best.

411
00:19:02,738 --> 00:19:04,805
We only have the rifle training left.

412
00:19:04,871 --> 00:19:06,871
- The rifles.
- Listen to them, Seo-jin.

413
00:19:15,405 --> 00:19:17,038
CUSTOMIZABLE THANKS TO MODULAR DESIGN

414
00:19:17,105 --> 00:19:18,838
SIMILAR LAYOUT AS M16,
THE RIFLE THE TRIO IS USED TO

415
00:19:18,905 --> 00:19:21,838
SINCE THEY'RE USING A RIFLE,
THE TARGET IS PLACED FURTHER AWAY

416
00:19:21,905 --> 00:19:24,005
(ROUGHLY 21.5 M AWAY)
TARGET

417
00:19:24,071 --> 00:19:27,505
FOR THE RIFLE BET,
THEY'LL SHOOT SITTING DOWN

418
00:19:35,705 --> 00:19:36,771
STARTING WITH THIS SHOT

419
00:19:36,838 --> 00:19:38,105
Hey, it has a heavier recoil.

420
00:19:38,171 --> 00:19:42,338
SEO-JIN SHOOTS IN RAPID SUCCESSION
WITHOUT HESITATION

421
00:19:42,405 --> 00:19:44,571
THE RESULT IS DELIVERED TO YOU RIGHT AWAY

422
00:19:44,638 --> 00:19:46,638
Not a single miss, right?

423
00:19:46,705 --> 00:19:49,438
AVERAGE SCORE: 8.7 POINTS

424
00:19:49,505 --> 00:19:51,905
Still, you never shot
the white circle in the center.

425
00:19:51,971 --> 00:19:53,638
JEERING

426
00:19:53,705 --> 00:19:55,271
- Which lane are you going to use?
- Then again…

427
00:19:55,338 --> 00:19:56,405
Go for Lane 3.

428
00:19:56,471 --> 00:19:57,838
HE'S STILL PROUD AND WANTS A PHOTO

429
00:19:57,905 --> 00:19:59,271
I'm going to use Lane 3.

430
00:19:59,338 --> 00:20:01,471
He's using Lane 3.

431
00:20:01,538 --> 00:20:03,471
- Will you shoot sitting down too?
- Yes.

432
00:20:03,538 --> 00:20:05,105
It's too tiring otherwise.

433
00:20:05,605 --> 00:20:09,271
I refuse to give credit
to guys who shoot sitting down.

434
00:20:09,338 --> 00:20:10,805
ONE CREW MEMBER EXCLAIMS

435
00:20:10,871 --> 00:20:13,471
A FAVORABLE RESPONSE WILL MAKE YUNG-SUK
DO A GTA CHARACTER IMPRESSION

436
00:20:14,671 --> 00:20:18,171
DAE-JU IS UNPERTURBED
AND SHOOTS WHILE SITTING DOWN

437
00:20:18,238 --> 00:20:19,271
It's Lane 3.

438
00:20:19,338 --> 00:20:20,338
CHECKING THE RESULT

439
00:20:21,171 --> 00:20:23,005
HOW ARE YOU SUCH A GOOD SHOT, DAE-JU?

440
00:20:23,071 --> 00:20:24,838
All right. That's great.

441
00:20:24,905 --> 00:20:26,771
- He's done well.
- The game's over.

442
00:20:26,838 --> 00:20:29,571
AVERAGE SCORE: 9.2 POINTS

443
00:20:29,638 --> 00:20:31,571
Prepare for a penalty, Seo-jin.

444
00:20:32,071 --> 00:20:34,938
Mr. Defense Security Command
lost to Mr. Full-time Reserve.

445
00:20:35,005 --> 00:20:37,471
Turns out Korean full-time reserves
are a force to reckon with.

446
00:20:39,238 --> 00:20:41,005
YUNG-SUK DIDN'T CATCH THAT

447
00:20:41,071 --> 00:20:42,638
You'll be shooting standing?

448
00:20:42,705 --> 00:20:44,838
Of course, I'm all about style.

449
00:20:44,905 --> 00:20:47,238
MR. KATUSA PRIORITIZES LOOKING COOL

450
00:20:47,305 --> 00:20:51,205
- He's going overboard again.
- That won't work out. It's pretty rough.

451
00:20:51,805 --> 00:20:55,571
MR. "I'M-ALL-ABOUT-STYLE" KATUSA
TAKING OVER-THE-TOP SHOTS

452
00:20:55,638 --> 00:20:58,038
He must be feeling impatient,
judging by the rapid-fire shots.

453
00:20:58,105 --> 00:21:00,305
Isn't it tough to shoot standing up?

454
00:21:00,371 --> 00:21:03,538
- He shot back-to-back because it's tough.
- I should get an extra point for that.

455
00:21:03,605 --> 00:21:04,871
No way.

456
00:21:05,471 --> 00:21:07,105
YUNG-SUK GETS HIS RESULT RIGHT THEN

457
00:21:07,171 --> 00:21:09,971
- So Yung-suk comes in last.
- Yes, dead last.

458
00:21:10,038 --> 00:21:11,605
AVERAGE SCORE: 8.2 POINTS

459
00:21:11,671 --> 00:21:13,105
LAST PLACE CONFIRMED

460
00:21:13,171 --> 00:21:14,738
I still shot standing up.

461
00:21:25,971 --> 00:21:27,571
We'll shoot standing up.

462
00:21:33,438 --> 00:21:34,471
You heard him, right?

463
00:21:35,238 --> 00:21:38,338
MR. KATUSA HAS AN EDGE IN DIPLOMACY TOO

464
00:21:38,405 --> 00:21:41,838
Still, the third target stands out.

465
00:21:41,905 --> 00:21:43,405
Yes, especially these two shots.

466
00:21:43,938 --> 00:21:45,071
All right, then.

467
00:21:45,138 --> 00:21:46,538
WITH DAE-JU'S PROUD LAUGHTER

468
00:21:48,371 --> 00:21:50,338
YUNG-SUK, 8.2 POINTS
SEO-JIN, 8.7 POINTS

469
00:21:50,405 --> 00:21:51,838
DAE-JU, 9.2 POINTS

470
00:21:52,338 --> 00:21:54,405
DAE-JU WINS!

471
00:21:55,638 --> 00:21:58,205
I didn't see this coming.

472
00:21:58,905 --> 00:22:01,505
I can't believe
we couldn't beat Mr. Full-time Reserve.

473
00:22:02,305 --> 00:22:06,171
Dae-ju must've received training
throughout his service.

474
00:22:06,238 --> 00:22:09,105
He must have done some shooting
as a reservist.

475
00:22:09,171 --> 00:22:12,171
Everyone does at least twice a year,
once in summer and once in winter.

476
00:22:12,238 --> 00:22:13,238
Not me.

477
00:22:13,305 --> 00:22:15,305
I've never handled a gun
during my service.

478
00:22:15,371 --> 00:22:16,705
Where did this excuse come from?

479
00:22:16,771 --> 00:22:18,738
I just hadn't held one
after the initial training.

480
00:22:18,805 --> 00:22:21,205
Supply management
was my main focus back then,

481
00:22:21,271 --> 00:22:23,705
- so I'm skilled--
- Did you actually supply goods, though?

482
00:22:23,771 --> 00:22:26,538
I was a supply specialist.

483
00:22:26,605 --> 00:22:30,805
The expert told us I did great
considering how I was standing up.

484
00:22:30,871 --> 00:22:31,905
Secure us ammo, Mr. Specialist.

485
00:22:31,971 --> 00:22:32,905
THE OUTDOOR RANGE REACHED

486
00:22:34,538 --> 00:22:38,505
I bet we look hilarious like this.

487
00:22:38,571 --> 00:22:40,771
TARGETS WILL BE LAUNCHED EVERY WHICH WAY

488
00:22:40,838 --> 00:22:43,938
AND THE TRIO WILL HAVE TO SHOOT THEM
FOR THIS FUN ACTIVITY

489
00:22:44,005 --> 00:22:46,971
OUTDOOR SHOTGUN SHOOTING RANGE

490
00:22:59,638 --> 00:23:01,005
OUTGOER
A TARGET THAT FLIES AWAY FROM THE SHOOTER

491
00:23:01,071 --> 00:23:05,371
CROSSER
A TARGET THAT FLIES ACROSS THE SHOOTER

492
00:23:05,438 --> 00:23:06,738
What are we supposed to do?

493
00:23:09,305 --> 00:23:10,371
THESE NOVICES WILL TRY OUTGOERS

494
00:23:10,438 --> 00:23:12,105
- How did he do that?
- He made it look so easy.

495
00:23:13,071 --> 00:23:15,605
A WELL-BALANCED LIGHTWEIGHT SHOTGUN
SUITED TO CLAY SHOOTING AND HUNTING

496
00:23:16,671 --> 00:23:17,605
It's a competition.

497
00:23:17,671 --> 00:23:18,605
THEY GET A 4-TARGET ROUND EACH

498
00:23:43,438 --> 00:23:45,205
SPECIAL LESSON FOR DOWNHEARTED SEO-JIN

499
00:24:02,171 --> 00:24:03,338
SO YOUR LINE OF SIGHT ALIGNS WITH THE GUN

500
00:24:03,405 --> 00:24:05,871
What did he say?
Interpret for us, Seo-jin.

501
00:24:06,871 --> 00:24:07,938
He's not telling us.

502
00:24:08,005 --> 00:24:08,938
You're hogging it?

503
00:24:09,438 --> 00:24:12,271
LEARN ENGLISH TO SURVIVE
IN THE HARSH WORLD OF COMPETITION

504
00:24:14,738 --> 00:24:16,838
FIRST SUCCESS!

505
00:24:18,405 --> 00:24:20,705
HIS SKILL HAS GREATLY IMPROVED
THANKS TO THE SPOT-ON TIP

506
00:24:20,771 --> 00:24:23,205
SEO-JIN IS FINALLY SMILING

507
00:24:25,305 --> 00:24:26,971
2 POINTS

508
00:24:27,038 --> 00:24:29,538
CONTESTANT NO. 2
MR. KATUSA, YUNG-SUK

509
00:24:31,138 --> 00:24:32,205
Hey, I missed.

510
00:24:35,171 --> 00:24:37,038
I can't seem to hit it. It's difficult.

511
00:24:37,105 --> 00:24:38,605
JUST LIKE SEO-JIN
THE BULLET FLEW RIGHT UNDER THE TARGET

512
00:24:38,671 --> 00:24:39,505
Try again.

513
00:24:39,571 --> 00:24:41,605
Try again. You were pretty close.

514
00:24:42,671 --> 00:24:44,205
Save your empty words of comfort.

515
00:24:44,271 --> 00:24:45,938
Come on, it wasn't like that.

516
00:24:48,538 --> 00:24:50,305
A FRUSTRATED GROAN

517
00:24:52,338 --> 00:24:53,438
Seo-jin.

518
00:24:54,471 --> 00:24:55,738
Try again.

519
00:24:59,338 --> 00:25:01,805
AT LEAST HIS FINAL SHOT HIT THE MARK

520
00:25:01,871 --> 00:25:03,071
KATUSA'S HONOR IS RESTORED

521
00:25:03,138 --> 00:25:04,905
- Isn't it fun?
- It is.

522
00:25:06,905 --> 00:25:08,738
1 POINT

523
00:25:15,938 --> 00:25:19,771
THE DEFENDING CHAMPION UNDER STRESS

524
00:25:24,205 --> 00:25:27,138
THE NERVES GOT DAE-JU USING KONGLISH

525
00:25:30,671 --> 00:25:32,938
THE INSTRUCTOR SEEMS TO READ FACES

526
00:25:40,138 --> 00:25:43,171
That's how you do it.
I'm learning from Dae-ju.

527
00:25:46,038 --> 00:25:47,638
ANOTHER HIT!

528
00:25:47,705 --> 00:25:49,805
BEWILDERED BY HIS SUCCESS

529
00:25:49,871 --> 00:25:52,171
MR. DEFENSE SECURITY COMMAND
AND MR. KATUSA ARE SPEECHLESS

530
00:25:52,238 --> 00:25:53,671
Turns out this isn't easy.

531
00:25:54,338 --> 00:25:56,671
We have to do it like Dae-ju.

532
00:25:57,605 --> 00:25:59,638
Our gun should follow the target's path.

533
00:25:59,705 --> 00:26:00,938
I see.

534
00:26:01,005 --> 00:26:03,038
THEIR ROUNDS ARE ALREADY OVER

535
00:26:03,105 --> 00:26:05,205
CURRENTLY, SEO-JIN IS IN THE LEAD
WITH ONLY 2 POINTS

536
00:26:05,271 --> 00:26:07,005
DAE-JU WINS IF HE HITS ONE MORE TARGET

537
00:26:10,738 --> 00:26:12,871
MR. EVERYDAY SOLDIER WINS

538
00:26:19,338 --> 00:26:21,005
A SATISFIED PUFF OF AIR

539
00:26:22,338 --> 00:26:24,205
TRAINING MATTERS MORE
THAN YOUR ASSIGNED POST

540
00:26:24,271 --> 00:26:25,705
What's with him?

541
00:26:27,738 --> 00:26:29,871
4 OUT OF 4, A PERFECT SCORE!

542
00:26:29,938 --> 00:26:32,305
DAE-JU IS CROWNED THE FINAL WINNER

543
00:26:32,371 --> 00:26:34,971
WRAPPING UP THE SHOOTING EXPERIENCE
WITH A COMMEMORATIVE PHOTO

544
00:26:35,038 --> 00:26:37,005
Put your foot on the cart, Dae-ju.

545
00:26:37,071 --> 00:26:39,305
A POSE TO CELEBRATE THE WIN

546
00:26:39,371 --> 00:26:41,105
He'd end up looking more awkward.

547
00:26:41,171 --> 00:26:42,471
TEARS

548
00:26:45,671 --> 00:26:48,105
THE ENJOYABLE SHOOTING EXPERIENCE ENDS

549
00:26:48,171 --> 00:26:50,405
FINAL ACTIVITY FOR TODAY

550
00:26:50,471 --> 00:26:53,071
Where are we headed again?
Remind me of the place's name.

551
00:26:53,138 --> 00:26:56,005
- Gas Monkey Garage.
- Gas Monkey Garage.

552
00:26:56,071 --> 00:26:58,505
The place is run by Richard Rawlings.

553
00:26:58,571 --> 00:27:03,438
There was this TV show
called <i>Fast N' Loud</i> about a decade ago.

554
00:27:03,505 --> 00:27:06,038
- That's the title of the show?
- Yes, <i>Fast N' Loud.</i>

555
00:27:06,738 --> 00:27:11,605
It was about restoring
and customizing classic cars.

556
00:27:11,671 --> 00:27:15,105
The show captured the whole process
of the cars getting modernized.

557
00:27:15,171 --> 00:27:17,338
It was very popular.

558
00:27:17,405 --> 00:27:22,471
The business boomed,
and the garage expanded.

559
00:27:22,538 --> 00:27:24,405
So people started visiting the place.

560
00:27:24,471 --> 00:27:25,771
NOW IT'S A TOURIST ATTRACTION

561
00:27:25,838 --> 00:27:29,271
I'd say our activities today
are very Texan.

562
00:27:29,338 --> 00:27:31,471
THE ITINERARY SOMEHOW FILLS YOU WITH PRIDE

563
00:27:31,538 --> 00:27:34,105
Starting from the way we're dressed.

564
00:27:34,171 --> 00:27:36,871
We're visiting this place
to see classic cars.

565
00:27:37,505 --> 00:27:39,971
We're also staying at a ranch house.

566
00:27:41,838 --> 00:27:43,438
YUNG-SUK, ONLY BEEN HERE FOR 2 DAYS

567
00:27:43,505 --> 00:27:45,505
There it is. "Gas Monkey Garage."

568
00:27:45,571 --> 00:27:47,305
EXCITED

569
00:27:52,238 --> 00:27:57,338
- Is this the place that was on TV?
- Look at the skid marks.

570
00:27:57,405 --> 00:27:59,571
I told you.
Look, that's from the drifting cars.

571
00:27:59,638 --> 00:28:01,005
CLEAR SKID MARKS IN THE FRONT YARD

572
00:28:01,071 --> 00:28:02,705
They drift here in the yard.

573
00:28:02,771 --> 00:28:07,005
RICHARD'S SIGNATURE CEREMONY
AFTER REMODELING A CAR

574
00:28:07,071 --> 00:28:09,438
IS TO TAKE IT OUT FOR A DRIFT

575
00:28:10,238 --> 00:28:11,838
SO CHARISMATIC

576
00:28:14,271 --> 00:28:16,305
HIS TEAMMATES YELL IN EXCITEMENT

577
00:28:19,038 --> 00:28:21,505
THIS PLACE IS FILLED WITH WILD ENERGY

578
00:28:21,571 --> 00:28:22,671
ARRIVED WITH A RACING HEART

579
00:28:22,738 --> 00:28:26,271
- I'm a Texan now, spiritually.
- There are mechanics working on a car.

580
00:28:26,338 --> 00:28:27,905
APPRECIATIVE EXCLAMATIONS

581
00:28:28,571 --> 00:28:30,305
What do you think that car is?

582
00:28:30,371 --> 00:28:33,138
- The car he's wiping now…
- What's the make of that?

583
00:28:33,205 --> 00:28:34,805
From the back, it looks like Testarossa.

584
00:28:34,871 --> 00:28:36,338
- Right?
- Yes.

585
00:28:36,405 --> 00:28:39,005
Let me tell you
about the Ferrari Testarossa.

586
00:28:39,071 --> 00:28:42,705
Back in the '80s,
it was featured in <i>Miami Vice</i>

587
00:28:43,371 --> 00:28:46,371
as the protagonist's car.

588
00:28:46,438 --> 00:28:49,171
That turned Testarossa
into a sensation in the US.

589
00:28:49,238 --> 00:28:52,838
Everyone who was anyone made
an appearance on <i>Miami Vice</i> as a cameo.

590
00:28:52,905 --> 00:28:54,871
It's like we're shooting a show
for the US viewers.

591
00:28:54,938 --> 00:28:55,938
HEADING INSIDE AFTER REMINISCING

592
00:28:58,705 --> 00:29:01,138
DIMPLES DEEPENED
AFTER MEETING HIS FAVORITE CELEBRITY

593
00:29:12,005 --> 00:29:13,471
INTRODUCTION FINISHED

594
00:29:26,671 --> 00:29:29,171
HE'LL SHOW THEM
THE TESTAROSSA FROM EARLIER

595
00:29:36,738 --> 00:29:37,905
PAUSING

596
00:29:45,505 --> 00:29:47,671
A SUDDEN TRANSITION
INTO AN AMERICAN REALITY SHOW

597
00:31:02,171 --> 00:31:04,238
AS POWERFUL AS 2 F1 CARS COMBINED

598
00:31:07,338 --> 00:31:08,671
My gosh. A glass roof.

599
00:31:11,771 --> 00:31:14,971
A TEST DRIVE WITH A RACING HEART

600
00:31:15,938 --> 00:31:18,538
A MONSTROUS ROAR

601
00:31:21,738 --> 00:31:25,338
THAT'S DEAFENING!

602
00:31:30,405 --> 00:31:33,738
THIS HAPPY FANBOY'S DIMPLES
HAVE DEEPENED TWICE AS MUCH

603
00:31:33,805 --> 00:31:36,471
Are they rebuilding the car, Seo-jin?

604
00:31:36,538 --> 00:31:38,038
Yes, practically from scratch.

605
00:31:42,771 --> 00:31:45,338
WE OFFER DISCOUNTS

606
00:31:57,138 --> 00:31:58,671
THE DOOR SWINGS OPEN TO THE FRONT

607
00:31:58,738 --> 00:32:00,938
It's so cute.

608
00:32:19,105 --> 00:32:21,305
THIS SUPERCAR IS LOVED BY SUPERSTARS

609
00:32:21,371 --> 00:32:23,205
LIKE MICHAEL JORDAN AND ELTON JOHN

610
00:32:32,505 --> 00:32:35,105
MODIFIED TO HAVE A WHOPPING 6 WHEELS

611
00:32:46,138 --> 00:32:49,305
YOU USUALLY SPIN THE 2 REAR WHEELS
TO CREATE SMOKE AND A LOUD NOISE

612
00:32:49,371 --> 00:32:52,438
BUT THIS HIGH-PERFORMANCE TUNING CAR
CAN SPIN ITS 4 REAR WHEELS FOR A BURNOUT

613
00:33:31,571 --> 00:33:32,971
I'm loving this car too.

614
00:33:33,038 --> 00:33:34,971
Hey, that's a sleek one.

615
00:33:40,538 --> 00:33:43,505
DOMINIC FROM FAST & FURIOUS
DROVE THIS MODEL

616
00:33:59,105 --> 00:34:02,371
A JAW-DROPPING PRICE RANGE

617
00:34:16,405 --> 00:34:19,571
AN ASTOUNDING COLLECTION

618
00:34:20,571 --> 00:34:25,971
FROM LATEST SPORTS CARS
TO RARE CLASSIC CARS

619
00:34:31,638 --> 00:34:32,671
It's a beauty.

620
00:34:32,738 --> 00:34:34,038
Look at all the arrangements.

621
00:34:34,105 --> 00:34:35,471
EVEN SIMON COWELL LOVES THIS CLASSIC CAR

622
00:34:39,238 --> 00:34:41,971
CAR THAT WAS FEATURED
IN SEASON 1, EPISODE 1 OF FAST N' LOUD

623
00:34:42,038 --> 00:34:44,905
1931 FORD MODEL A HOT ROD

624
00:34:52,805 --> 00:34:55,805
1978 PONTIAC FIREBIRD TRANS AM

625
00:35:00,338 --> 00:35:02,805
And I had to pay 65,000 for this one.

626
00:35:02,871 --> 00:35:04,538
THE PRICE HAS RISEN EXPONENTIALLY

627
00:35:04,605 --> 00:35:05,871
What is this thing?

628
00:35:13,271 --> 00:35:15,005
DRAGSTER
NICKNAMED "SLINGSHOT" FOR ITS LOOK

629
00:35:15,071 --> 00:35:17,305
UNIQUE DESIGN WITH ENGINE AND REAR WHEELS
IN FRONT OF THE DRIVER

630
00:35:17,371 --> 00:35:19,305
BACK IN THE 1950S AND 1960S,
IT WAS CONSIDERED EFFECTIVE

631
00:35:19,871 --> 00:35:22,205
THE SHOWCASE
OF RARE COLLECTIBLES CONTINUES

632
00:35:22,271 --> 00:35:23,638
I bet this costs the most.

633
00:35:23,705 --> 00:35:25,438
1939 LINCOLN ZEPHYR

634
00:35:26,005 --> 00:35:28,571
1977 FERRARI 308 GTB

635
00:35:29,171 --> 00:35:31,471
1967 SHELBY MUSTANG GT500

636
00:35:31,538 --> 00:35:34,571
1963 CHEVROLET CORVETTE

637
00:35:40,971 --> 00:35:44,971
RICHARD'S COLLECTION INCLUDES
BOTH CLASSIC AND MODERN CARS

638
00:36:16,071 --> 00:36:18,438
HOPING FOR A REUNION WITH RICHARD

639
00:37:09,938 --> 00:37:14,938
Subtitle translation by: Jeongwoo Kim
